cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Klein Auto Research in your work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Klein Auto Research"
abstract: >-
  An agentic, visualization-first ML research framework for actuaries and data
  scientists: a six-stage study lifecycle (consult, data gate, method gate,
  ledgered experiment loop, insight synthesis, teaching tutorial) that turns
  hours of disciplined experiments on your own data into honest verdicts about
  where a modeling method pays.
authors:
  - family-names: "Shan"
    given-names: "Xiang"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-07-10"
url: "https://github.com/Xiang-Shan/klein-auto-research"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Xiang-Shan/klein-auto-research"
keywords:
  - machine learning
  - actuarial science
  - research framework
  - agentic workflows
  - experiment tracking
references:
